### In-Memory LocalStorage Adapter for Supabase SSR

Source: https://context7.com/supabase/ssr/llms.txt

Provides a `localStorage`-compatible adapter that stores data in memory. This is useful for server environments where native `localStorage` is unavailable, particularly for managing user authentication tokens in tokens-only mode.

```typescript
import { memoryLocalStorageAdapter } from '@supabase/ssr'

// Create in-memory storage for server-side user data
const memoryStorage = memoryLocalStorageAdapter()

const supabase = createServerClient(
  process.env.SUPABASE_URL!,
  process.env.SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!,
  {
    cookies: {
      getAll: () => request.cookies.getAll(),
      setAll: (cookies) => response.cookies.setAll(cookies)
    },
    auth: {
      // Use memory storage for user object when using tokens-only mode
      userStorage: memoryStorage
    }
  }
)

// Storage is scoped to this instance only
memoryStorage.setItem('key', 'value')
console.log(memoryStorage.getItem('key')) // 'value'
memoryStorage.removeItem('key')
console.log(memoryStorage.getItem('key')) // null

// Use with custom initial state
const preloadedStorage = memoryLocalStorageAdapter({
  'supabase.auth.token': '{"access_token":"..."}',
  'app.preferences': '{"theme":"dark"}'
})

console.log(preloadedStorage.getItem('app.preferences'))
// '{"theme":"dark"}'
```

